Section 1:
1 L.D. 294
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 TAXATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 194, L.D. 294, “An Act to Expand
10 Municipal Volunteer Program Eligibility Requirements in the Municipal Property Tax
11 Assistance Laws”
12 Amend the bill by inserting before section 1 the following:
13 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §5122, sub-§2, ¶EE, as corrected by RR 2009, c. 2, §111, is
14 amended to read:
15 EE. To the extent included in federal adjusted gross income, an amount constituting
16 benefits received under a municipal property tax assistance program established
17 pursuant to section 6232, subsection subsections 1‑A and 1-B;'
18 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1-B in the first blocked paragraph in the last
19 2 lines (page 1, lines 32 and 33 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "full-time emergency
20 medical services person" and inserting the following: 'worker employed 40 hours per week
21 at the state minimum wage'
22 Amend the bill by inserting after section 2 the following:
23 'Sec. 3. 36 MRSA §6232, sub-§1-C is enacted to read:
24 1-C. Single benefit. A volunteer may not participate in both a program established
25 pursuant to subsection 1-A and a program established pursuant to subsection 1-B in the
26 same tax year.'
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment adjusts the deductions to individual income to account for the
3311 expanded municipal volunteer program. The amendment amends the definition of
3322 "volunteer emergency medical services person" by adjusting the maximum income a
3333 volunteer emergency medical services person may receive to be eligible for participation
Page 1 - 132LR0286(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 194, L.D. 294
314 in the expanded municipal volunteer program. The amendment restricts participants from
325 receiving a benefit from both municipal property tax assistance programs in the same year.
Page 2 - 132LR0286(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
